om a single charge or battery unit.","<strong>Mobility</strong><br/>The typical cheap mobility scooter can achieve average walking speeds, whereas the fastest mobility scooter can facilitate paces of up to 10 miles an hour. This speed is constrained by the battery, which can offer you a range of 10 to nearly 30 miles on a single charge. The speed of the scooters ensures you won’t be hindered by any ailments and can easily reach destinations without fear of the battery losing its charge. In addition, the turning radius on a unit greatly impacts its mobility. Many models allow you to make tight turns, like turning into an aisle at the grocery store, with relative ease.","<strong>Warranty</strong><br/>You can expect to see multiple types of warranties coupled together for a handicap scooter. There’s a drive train warranty that covers critical components such as transaxle, motor and electronic elements. Then you can also expect a structural warranty that protects frame components such as platform, seat post and frame failures. Some warranty exclusions may exist that won’t cover replacing parts like brake pads, tires, upholstery and batteries.","Mobility scooters are fundamental in the lives of those who suffer from handicaps and full-body ailments. With the help of a scooter, a person can go from no mobility to being more mobile than the average person. It’s important to consider a scooter’s ease of portability, battery life and warranty options when researching options to make sure you’re getting the best assistance around."]},"id":"858c0608-cb51-4b7e-aa95-9e855900adb4","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Related Product Reviews"},"id":"3ae956e3-2454-4bc3-944b-3ebc56a37fc0","type":"heading"},{"data":{"items":["<a href=\"http://click.linksynergy.com/link?id=Cty0dj6o3sg&offerid=219490.95545&type=2&murl=https%3A%2F%2Fspinlife.affiliatetechnology.com%2Fredirect.php%3Fnt_id%3D1%26url%3Dhttp%253A%252F%252Fwww.spinlife.com%252FAfikim-Breeze-C-4-Wheel-4-Wheel-Scooter%252Fspec.cfm%